            "content": {
                "sections": [
                    {
                        "title": "Significant Common Ground",
                        "content": "<p>Meditation tech and cyberdelics have substantial overlap. Many apps use technology to support contemplation. The boundaries aren't always clear, and that's okay.</p>",
                        "triggerLabel": "Meditation Tech"
                    },
                    {
                        "title": "Simple Meditation Apps",
                        "media": {
                            "type": "image",
                            "src": "../assets/images/module1/lesson4/meditation_apps.jpg",
                            "alt": "Phone displaying meditation app interface"
                        },
                        "mediaLayout": "left",
                        "content": "<p>Apps like Headspace/Calm are valuable for mindfulness but typically don't use immersive VR or biofeedback to intentionally create altered states. They are <strong>meditation tech</strong>, not cyberdelic.</p>",
                        "triggerLabel": "Cyberdelic Territory"
                    },
                    {
                        "title": "VR Meditation With Biofeedback",
                        "media": {
                            "type": "image",
                            "src": "../assets/images/module1/lesson4/venn_diagram.jpg",
                            "alt": "Venn Diagram: Meditation Tech vs. Cyberdelics overlap"
                        },
                        "mediaLayout": "full",
                        "content": "<p>When practice moves into immersive VR with biofeedback that responds to your state, enabling profound altered states, you've crossed into <strong>cyberdelic territory</strong>. Tech becomes a catalyst, not just a delivery mechanism.</p>",
                        "triggerLabel": "Intensity Scale"
                    },
                    {
                        "title": "The Intensity Question",
                        "content": "<p>It's a spectrum. How immersive is it? How sophisticated is the biofeedback? How profound are the intended states? The more intense and intentional, the more cyberdelic.</p>",
                        "triggerLabel": "Both Valid"
                    },
                    {
                        "title": "Both Are Valid",
                        "content": "<p>This isn't about one being better. Simple apps serve millions. Cyberdelics offer deeper exploration. The field benefits from tools at different intensity levels.</p>",
                        "triggerLabel": "Categorize It"
                    }
                ]
            }
        },
